-- Downer EDI Said to Mandate National Australia, RBS for A$400 Million Loans
-- B y   S a r a h   M c D o n a l d
-- 2010-09-29T05:24:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/downer-edi-said-to-mandate-national-australia-rbs-for-a-400-million-loans.html
Downer EDI Ltd. , an Australian
engineering company, hired National Australia Bank Ltd. and
Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc to help it arrange A$400
million ($387 million) of loans, a person familiar with the
matter said.  Downer will use the proceeds to refinance existing  debt  and
may seek loans with maturities of three and four years, the
person said, asking not to be named as the matter is private.  Downer, based in Sydney, has A$390 million of revolving
loans maturing in June 2011, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Sarah McDonald  in Sydney at 
 smcdonald23@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will McSheehy at 
 wmcsheehy@bloomberg.net . 